feed.title: Neds Corner - Birds
feed.subtitle: Area incorporating (ie. birds seen from) the Neds Corner property (Trust for Nature) and the adjoining Murray River frontage.

entry.title: Certhionyx variegatus
entry.content: A small flock (<10) feeding over the revegetation area near the Sturt Highway.

entry.title: Barnardius zonarius barnardi
entry.content: Feeding under exotic trees near the homestead.

entry.title: Acanthiza nana
entry.content: Secretive and difficult to photograph on this occasion.

entry.title: Pomatostomus ruficeps
entry.content: Captured on motion-sensor camera at bird bath.

entry.title: Hirundo neoxena
entry.content: On the roof of the shearers' quarters at Neds Corner. Nesting also in the same building.

entry.title: Cacatua galerita
entry.content: Curiously, not commonly encountered at Neds Corner.

entry.title: Hydroprogne caspia
entry.content: Hunting along the Potterwalkagee Creek and Murray River.

entry.title: Epthianura albifrons
entry.content: Ordinary photo (very long distance away) but confirms the species.

entry.title: Plectorhyncha lanceolata
entry.content: Feeding on grubs hidden behind the seeds in the large pods of the Brachychiton tree in front of the Neds Corner homestead.

entry.title: Ardea pacifica
entry.content: Ordinary pic but useful as confirmation of the record, a new record for the Neds Corner birds collection. Far away and flew off before I could get close.

entry.title: Egretta novaehollandiae
entry.content: Ordinary pic but useful as confirmation of the record, a new record for the Neds Corner birds collection. Far away and flew off before I could get close.

entry.title: Phalacrocorax carbo
entry.content: Photographed from the Neds Corner homestead.
